race.comment: Big field whittled down but should still be good early pressure. That will help CLIODHNA MAEVE (5) who has had a few goes now and is overdue but looks well placed. Has found the line strongly both runs this time in and looks tough to stop. RAZOR'S MAGIC (7) on the other hand is a speedy mare who will be up front. Another overdue for a win but looks well placed here off the low draw and will take catching. INSAIN LADY (11) is a speed type drawn low and will give a sight.  ZEMOREYA (15) was well in the market on debut at Ipswich and settled off speed, circled deep and was fair to the line. Better for the experience and extra trip a plus. Expecting a better run.
